-- Dependency that merely DECLARES a PAYLOAD ctor `Guardy.GBool Int` (arity 1).  The
-- emitter folds ALL modules' DData into one bare-name ctor table (`ctorArities`
-- over every DData), so this declaration alone makes lib's payload `GBool` collide
-- with entry's NULLARY `Gty.GBool` — no construction of it is needed.  The oracle
-- (structural, no arity table) never constructs `Guardy`, so it stays correct; the
-- collision is purely in the emitter's table.  `useOther` is the only thing entry
-- imports, keeping lib in the module graph.
public export data Other = Wrap Int
public export data Guardy = GBool Int | GBind Int

export useOther : Other -> Int
useOther (Wrap n) = n
